  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: '  This letter is from Paul, a prisoner for preaching the Good News
        about Christ Jesus, and from our brother Timothy.I am writing to Philemon,
        our beloved co-worker, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and to our sister Apphia, and to our fellow soldier Archippus, and
        to the church that meets in your[[COMMENT(0)]] house.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: Throughout this letter, <b>you </b>and <b>your </b>are singular
          except in verses 3, 22, and 25.
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Thanksgiving and Prayer"
      content: 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you grace and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I always thank my God when I pray for you, Philemon, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "because I keep hearing about your faith in the Lord Jesus and your
        love for all of God\u2019s people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I am praying that you will put into action the generosity that
        comes from your faith as you understand and experience all the good things
        we have in Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Appeal for Onesimus"
      content: "Your love has given me much joy and comfort, my brother, for your
        kindness has often refreshed the hearts of God\u2019s people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why I am boldly asking a favor of you. I could demand it
        in the name of Christ because it is the right thing for you to do. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But because of our love, I prefer simply to ask you. Consider this
        as a request from me\u2014Paul, an old man and now also a prisoner for the
        sake of Christ Jesus.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: Or <b>a prisoner of Christ Jesus.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I appeal to you to show kindness to my child, Onesimus. I became
        his father in the faith while here in prison. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Onesimus[[COMMENT(0)]] hasn\u2019t been of much use to you in the
        past, but now he is very useful to both of us. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: "<b>Onesimus </b>means \u201Cuseful.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'I am sending him back to you, and with him comes my own heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I wanted to keep him here with me while I am in these chains for
        preaching the Good News, and he would have helped me on your behalf. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I didn\u2019t want to do anything without your consent. I wanted
        you to help because you were willing, not because you were forced. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It seems you lost Onesimus for a little while so that you could have
        him back forever. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He is no longer like a slave to you. He is more than a slave, for
        he is a beloved brother, especially to me. Now he will mean much more to
        you, both as a man and as a brother in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So if you consider me your partner, welcome him as you would welcome
        me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If he has wronged you in any way or owes you anything, charge it
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay it. And I won\u2019t
        mention that you owe me your very soul!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, my brother, please do me this favor[[COMMENT(0)]] for the Lord\u2019s
        sake. Give me this encouragement in Christ.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: Greek <b>onaimen, </b>a play on the name Onesimus.
    - title: 
      content: 'I am confident as I write this letter that you will do what I ask
        and even more! '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Greetings"
      content: "One more thing\u2014please prepare a guest room for me, for I am
        hoping that God will answer your prayers and let me return to you soon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends you his greetings. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my co-workers.  '
      comments: []
